  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Building Somali Disapora support to Somalia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">HIRDA is a UK based organisation led by Somalis from the Diaspora. It  supports education, women&#x2019;s empowerment and health programmes in Somalia, and runs educational programmes in the UK, funded by a BBC Children in Need grant.  The organisation is relatively strong in terms of its networks, membership and its partnerships in Somalia, and the Netherlands. The organisation lacks expertise in designing development projects, fundraising and in organisational development. It particularly seeks training in organisational management, proposal writing, project design and evaluation, donor identification, and ways to sustain its own future. It is currently staffed only by volunteers with a small administration budget covering rent and utilities.
This grant will facilitate a training programme enabling key individuals to attend relevant courses from providers such as INTRAC, Mango and BOND.  External consultants will run in-house training in capacity building and fundraising for all trustees and key volunteers, who will also be supported to give more time to building HIRDA&#x2019;s future. To have a realistic and achievable programme of training and consultancy-run workshops they were advised to extend the project timeframe to at least 20 months, to which they have willingly agreed. They have also tightened up their plans for the training programme, and this should be translated into a plan of action before the grant is made.</narrative>
  </description>
